abstract_str: durst spent the night before his arrest wandering around new orleans ' french quarter with his loaded .38 - caliber revolver in his pocket . a nightclub doorman has recalled a conversation with durst where he said he could n't come in the club , before he stumbled off down the street . john phillips , 32 , a doorman at the mahogany jazz hall burlesque and __absinthe__ house said durst revealed to him that he was carrying a weapon . durst 's apparent whispered confession on hbo could come back to haunt him -- or help him -- as he faces his murder charge .
